  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Advanced Race Guide pg. 189</em></p><h3 class=\"framing\"><img src=\"https://www.aonprd.com/images/PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif\" title=\"PFS Legal\" style=\"margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;\">Statistics</h3><p><strong>Cost</strong> 8 gp <strong>Weight</strong> 1 lb.</p><p><strong>Damage</strong> 1d3 (small), 1d4 (medium); <strong>Critical</strong> 19-20/x2; <strong>Range</strong> -; <strong>Type</strong> S; <strong>Special</strong> -</p><p><strong>Category</strong> Light; <strong>Proficiency</strong> Martial</p><h3 class=\"framing\">Description</h3><p>A sea-knife is a long-handled weapon with a short blade. It is designed to be strapped to the ankle or foot of the wielder, pointing downward and jutting out beyond the wearer's leg. Donning or removing a sea-knife is a full-round action. The wearer cannot use a leg with a sea-knife strapped to it for walking or running. A sea-knife can be used as a light melee weapon when the wielder is swimming, flying, or prone. This allows the wielder to use a two-handed weapon, or wield a weapon with one hand and carry a shield, and still make off-hand attacks with the sea-knife. Attacks made with a sea-knife take a -2 circumstance penalty on attack rolls in addition to all other attack penalties. </p>",
